That giving him both options had a 0.1% chance of working. Oh no, he taunted him...0.2% chance. I hoped Shroud would be like....a better villain. Everyone else in this game has a human side, might even make me believe that they think for themselves. So the problem is not that there wasnÂ´t a chance, there was just no chance of Robert doing that. Guess they couldnÂ´t fit that in the last episode anymore. As fun as the idea of an ending like that is, itÂ´s so goofy and unbelievable. 

Give him both, make him consider, make him waste a few moments because see someone else got a shot with him being distracted, that would have been fine. Make Visi noticeable to Robert somehow, that would have been better. Infact - they could open that choice just when we said we trust Visi, just like they locked choices with Blazer, when we didn't kiss her. Would have been at least something logical to reason and effect. A payoff somehow. But him getting taunted is just so easy. You can even see it in the animation itself, it flows much smoother that he opens his mask when he knows he won, when he knows he got the right one.

Also the last one, yeah he has no bullets left...but he got what he wanted? So why is he getting defeated like this? Why are his superpowered henchmen getting defeated like that? I donÂ´t get that. All explanations I see are just people grasping at their own headcanon to defend the game they like, but nobody can answer as to why it worked, it just did. And that I find unsatisfying. If its a villain that gets defeated by Todd Howard, I don't take him serious as a threat.

*_Invisi-gal/-bitch kills Shroud_** ~* Three great details to that part...
